{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "note": "retained_via_interfaces (31 rows) gave me the entire Step 4/5 narrowed-handle audit — raft.Backend.handle internal/storage/raft/backend.go:80, raft.forwardingClient internal/storage/raft/forwarding.go:115, v1compat.reconciler internal/multicluster/internal/controllers/v1compat/controller.go:81, ca.ConsulProvider agent/connect/ca/provider_consul.go:34, peerstream.subscriptionManager subscription_manager.go:46, submatview.LocalMaterializerDeps local_materializer.go:29, local.State agent/local/state.go:172 — every one of which I cited"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "note": "affected_via_composition gave the full 32-holder direct-*Server list with file:line (acl_endpoint.go:107 through v2_config_entry_exports_shim.go:23) that I transcribed verbatim into Step 4 group A"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "consul.Server", "note": "the 'inherits' list surfaced the locally-declared interfaces the Server satisfies — blockingquery.FSMServer:56, consul.serverDelegate gateway_locator.go:276, rate.ServersStatusProvider handler.go:195, reporting.ServerDelegate reporting.go:53, local.rpc state.go:164, agent.delegate agent.go:153 — which became the Step 5 route list"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "consul.NewServer", "note": "callees list gave the ordered construction phases I used for the Step 2 lifecycle table (setupRaft:917, setupRPC:1170, setupGRPCServices server_grpc.go:181, NewCAManager, xdscapacity.NewController, monitorLeadership leader.go:70)"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "note": "affected_tests (55 files) became the Step 7.3 'must update' list essentially unedited"},
    {"tool": "sense_status", "query": "(none)", "note": "top_namespaces and language split gave the Step 1 orientation numbers without opening a file"}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "note": "two retained_via_interfaces carrier attributions were wrong: usagemetrics.UsageMetricsReporter/Config and consul.OverviewManager were listed with carrier consul.caDelegateWithState, but sed of agent/consul/server.go:763,783 shows both are wired with s.fsm — they retain the FSM, not the Server. I had to correct these in the answer."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "note": "several carrier fields were placeholder-ish: agent.Agent (via 'delegate') and local.State (via 'rpc') were both attributed carrier consul.serverACLResolverBackend, when the actual runtime satisfier is *consul.Server itself (agent/agent.go:709). The 'via' iface was right, the carrier was a guess — the tool does flag this in retained_note."},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "consul.NewServer", "note": "returned verify_hint 'Zero callers found in the index' for a function that is called at agent/agent.go:704 — I only had the callees direction, but the hint text was flatly wrong for a symbol with a known caller"},
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "consul agent server struct that runs raft and RPC", "note": "top hit was consul.Server.rpcLogger (rpc.go:118), a trivial 2-line accessor; the actual target type consul.Server never appeared in the 15 results. I found it from the file path of the surrounding hits, not the ranking."}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "retained_via_interfaces gives holder ref + via + carrier but not the retaining field's own name or line — I needed 'which field, typed as what' for every Step 4/5 row, so I sed'd agent/consul/rate/handler.go:160-205, reporting.go:14-60, server_overview.go:15-35, provider_consul.go:28-45, backend.go:74-90, forwarding.go:110-120 to recover field names and exact lines"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "no wiring/assignment sites — the list said 'X retains Server via iface Y' but never where the value is assigned. I sed'd agent/consul/server_grpc.go:175-260 and 356-540 and grep'd 'func (s *Server) register' to get the ten handover lines (server_grpc.go:387,419,433,445,466,479-483,529,534) that Steps 3, 5 and 7 are built on"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "consul.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "composed_by was truncated at 22 rows with omitted_edges:168 and no way to page it; I got the complete 32-row set only from sense_blast's affected_via_composition in a separate call"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "consul.NewServer", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no shutdown counterpart and no goroutine/channel view — I grep'd 'shutdownCh' in agent/consul/server.go to find the 15 goroutine launch sites (531,568,570,666,670,781,784,787,788,822,832,865,1033) that are the core lifecycle hazard in Step 6"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no interface-satisfier resolution for ca.ConsulProvider.Delegate; I grep'd 'NewConsulProvider' and 'ConsulProvider{' to confirm the value is CAManager.delegate passed at leader_connect_ca.go:462"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "the grpc service Config structs' field names/lines weren't in the response — I batched sed over six agent/grpc-external/services/*/server.go files to get connectca:28-32, dataplane:24,26, serverdiscovery:22,24, peerstream:37, configentry:35,37"}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query_before": "sense_blast consul.Server (retained_via_interfaces returned 31 rows with carrier attributions)", "query_after": "Bash sed of agent/consul/server.go:755-800 and grep 'NewConsulProvider' to verify carriers", "hint": "retained_note: 'Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified.' — this is what made me spot-check, and it is exactly why I caught the usagemetrics/OverviewManager carriers being wrong"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query_before": "sense_graph consul.Server (composed_by truncated, omitted_edges:168, completeness verdict 'partial')", "query_after": "sense_blast consul.Server max_hops=3 — which returned the complete affected_via_composition list", "hint": "next_steps: '51 callers found — check blast radius before changing this symbol' plus completeness.verdict 'partial'"},
    {"tool": "sense_status", "query_before": "(session start)", "query_after": "sense_conventions domain=agent/consul, run in the same block as the first search", "hint": "next_steps: 'start of session — check project conventions' — the conventions call is what gave me the '22 of 70 interfaces declared in agent/consul' fact I used to frame the adapter pattern in Step 1"}
  ],
  "q4_value": "retained_via_interfaces on sense_blast(consul.Server). That one field is the entire ticket: it named holders in internal/storage/raft, internal/multicluster/.../v1compat, agent/connect/ca and agent/submatview whose files never import agent/consul and never spell *consul.Server — there is no grep that finds those, because the string you'd grep for does not appear in them. Recovering that set by hand would have meant enumerating every interface the Server satisfies and then finding each struct field typed as one, across 2,139 Go files.",
  "q5_improve": "Give each retained_via_interfaces row the retaining field's own name and line (not just the holder's struct line), and the assignment site where the value is handed over. Every row I reported needed 'field X at file:line, typed Y, assigned at Z' — the tool gave me one of those three, so I spent six follow-up sed/grep batches reconstructing the other two for 30+ rows. Also: drop or soften the carrier guess when confidence is low (agent.Agent's delegate attributed to serverACLResolverBackend was noise), and fix the 'Zero callers found in the index' hint firing on a callees-only sense_graph query.",
  "score": 9,
  "score_rationale": "retained_via_interfaces handed me eight cross-package holders (internal/storage/raft/backend.go:80, forwarding.go:115, v1compat/controller.go:81, provider_consul.go:34, local/state.go:172, submatview/local_materializer.go:29 and more) that are structurally ungreppable because those files never name consul.Server — that is Q1's core evidence for the 9-10 band; I dock one point because Q2 shows every row still needed a sed to recover the field name and the wiring site, and Q1 shows two carrier attributions were wrong enough that I had to publish corrections."
}

